body:
## Feature Request

### Motivation
_from discord discussion_
I m trying to implement centralised error handling
so i have enum which represents all errors
```rust
#[derive(Debug, thiserror::Error)]
pub enum Error { ... }
// From<Error>
pub type ApiError = (StatusCode, Json<Value>);
// used as return type from handlers
pub type ApiResult<T> = std::result::Result<T, ApiError>;
```
Also I have centralised type for error returning from handlers  and custom extractors (ApiError and ApiResult)

And impl from Error for ApiError. (all internal functions returns `Result<T, Error>`)
Simplified `From<Error> for ApiError`
```rust
impl From<Error> for ApiError {
    fn from(err: Error) -> Self {
        let status = match err {
            ...
            _ => StatusCode::INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR,
        };
        let payload = json!({"message": err.to_string()});
        (status, Json(payload))
    }
}
```
I'd like understand which header failed to be extracted in simple way like this:
```rust
Error::AxumTypedHeaderError(e) => match e.name {
  AUTHORIZATION => StatucCode::UNAUTHORIZED,
  _ => StatucCode::BAD_REQUEST
}
```

### Proposal

make fields `name` and `reason` public in struct `TypedHeaderRejection`

### Alternatives

`extract::typed_header` module is private (but `Reason` enum should be exported)
